SRADAR
======

The sradar command sweeps from a ship and reveals terrain in a radius
around it, updating your fog-of-war map. It's the ship-sourced
counterpart to 'radar' (radar STATION sectors) and 'lradar' (radar-
capable land units) — see 'info radar'/'info lradar'.

COMMAND
-------
  sradar SHIP-SPEC    Sweep from ship(s) matching SHIP-SPEC
  sradar *            Sweep from every owned ship
  sradar c            Sweep from every ship in fleet c (see 'info fleetadd')

SHIP-SPEC accepts a uid ("5"), a uid range ("0-5"), a comma list, "*"
for all of yours, "~" for ships with no fleet assigned, or a single
letter naming a fleet.

It's also available inline, mid-route, as the 'r' token in a
'navigate' command — sail a couple of hexes, take a radar reading,
keep going, all in one command. See 'info navigate'.

ELIGIBILITY
-----------
  Unlike 'lradar' (which needs a specific radar-capable land unit
  type), EVERY ship can sweep — there's no capability flag to check.
  Each hull just uses its own visual range stat (higher on more
  advanced ships). Sonar-equipped ships get no bonus here; their
  extra reach for finding submarines specifically is the separate
  'sonar' command (see 'info sonar').

RANGE
-----
  Range is determined by your technology level, the ship's visual
  range stat (a per-type constant), and the ship's current
  efficiency — same formula as 'radar'/'lradar':

    range = floor( vrnge * (50 + tech) / (200 + tech) * eff / 100 )
    minimum range: 1

WHAT YOU SEE
------------
  Same display rules as 'radar'/'lradar':
  Within range/3 of the ship:    actual sector mnemonic
  Beyond range/3 (outer ring):   '?' (something is there)
  Own sectors, sea, mountains, wasteland: always show actual mnemonic

  The center (the ship's own sector) is marked '0' on the display.

FOG OF WAR
----------
  Same fog-of-war rules as 'radar' — this sweep updates your bmap for
  the area scanned. Note this is separate from (and in addition to)
  the passive terrain reveal every ship already does automatically
  on each step of 'navigate' — 'sradar' just lets you take an
  on-demand reading without moving, or check a ship that's been
  sitting still.

EXAMPLES
--------
  sradar *          Sweep from every owned ship.
  sradar 5          Sweep from ship 5 only.
  sradar c          Sweep from every ship in fleet c.

